cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper discusses a communication protocol for computational RFID devices, which involves wireless communication and networking (cs.NI). The protocol also focuses on ensuring robustness and reliability in the face of power interruptions and varying channel conditions, which relates to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves system and control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT) in its design and implementation.
